input:
- number of lines to print option (command line): string
- number of lines to print value (command line): int

output:
print the last n lines to stdout

steps:
-read -n optional argument from command line input
-ensure that -n argument has a valid int value
-if no argument was provided at all:
 - make n = 10
-read line from stdin
-copy read line to buffer+offset position in the buffer array
-if the program encounters an EOF:
 - print the last n lines
